    {
      "id": "18b4750c-f3ba-8001-9ecc-c68e4dfbb6a2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The paper proposes a way of assembling intra-heterogenous and inter-homogenous groups for collaborative learning. The approach, using a Genetic Algorithm, was tested on a sample of 135 students (each student being represented as part of 3 features). Comparison against other methods of group formation shows not only computational feasibility but also improved student outcomes.",
      "raw": {
